This is the README file. This will include steps to compile and run the program.

Use provided makefile in Linux for easier compilation:
make

To run:
./simcity

Use this code for compliling anywhere:
g++ *.cpp -o simcity

To run the program after compiling:
Linux: ./simcity
Windows: simcity.exe


Requirements:
- g++
- Place all .cpp files, config1.txt, and region1.csv in the same directory.
- config1.txt format:
Region Layout:region1.csv
Time Limit:<limit>
Refresh Rate:<rate>


Example config1.txt:
Region Layout:region1.csv
Time Limit:20
Refresh Rate:1


Example region1.csv:
 , ,T,#,T,T,T, 
I,I,I,-,C,C,T, 
I,I,I,-,C,C,T,P
I,I,I,-,C,C,T, 
-,-,-,-,-,-,#,-
 , ,-,R,R,R,T, 
 , ,-,R,R,R, , 
 , ,-,R,R,R, , 


 Notes:
- This milestone implements Component 1:
    * Reads configuration file
    * Reads region file
    * Initializes simulation
    * Outputs initial region state (time step 0)